swiftness, strength)\r\nBadge:    On a plate within a belt Azure edged, buckled and inscribed with the Motto in letters Argent, an eagles head erased Azure beaked Gules.\r\nFlag: 	A banner of the Arms.\r\nStandard: 	The Arms in hoist, the fly per fess Argent and Sable charged with the Crest and the Badge.\r\nSource:  	Grant, Canadian Heraldic Authority, October 15, 2004.\r\nArtist: 	Ilona Jurkiewicz\r\nCalligrapher: 	Shirley Mangione','B.Sc.',NULL,'B.Sc.','University of Toronto',1,1,'Received a horizontal cut to the bridge of the nose from Brians kettle helm at a demonstration bout in Kitchener. No stitches were required. (2000)<br><br>\r\n\r\nIncurred an injury during an armoured bout, by a sword stab to the right hand between the index finger and thumb.  David was taken to Mount Sinai emergency where he received 5 stitches to close the wound. (2004)',1,'1998-05-18',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,'- problem knees (developed late 2005).',1,'14th century transitional harness, segmented breast plate, rivited mail shirt, hounskul helm with rivited mail aventail, metal uppers and vambraces, metal & leather gorget, segmented metal solarets, full leg armour including full metal greeves, metal hour-glass finger gauntlets.','Black gambeson, leather gorget, fencing mask, leather gauntlets augmented with metal demi-gauntlets, and leather & metal vambraces with cops.',NULL,4,'2005-05-01','Ossington',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'14th century garment with black long cotehardie, silver buttons front and sleeves, burgundy hood (nockert type), burgundy leather belt, French dagger and Towton arming sword, burgundy leggings and period footwear.','English longbow (65 lb) purchased from Quicks, 31in. bows, quiver, finger & forearm protection.',NULL,'David is the founder of AEMMA.\r\n\r\nEarned the National Coaching Certification Program (NCCP) Level 1 theory, a national coaching certification program part of the Coaching Association of Canada (2005).\r\n\r\nBasic First Aid & CPR (Feb 2006)'),(2,2,7,1,'AEMMA','Brian','A','McIlmoyle','Mr.','Mr. Brian McIlmoyle','1187 Roselawn Ave.','',NULL,'Toronto','ON','M6B 1C6','Canada','(416) 789-3515',NULL,NULL,'(416) 434-6482','brian.mcilmoyle@aemma.org',NULL,NULL,'http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_bmcilmoyle.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/m/mcilmoyle_80.jpg','Ontario Trustee','M',2,0,'Betty (Spike) Cavasan','1965-07-28',0,NULL,NULL,1,'Assumed','Purpure, on a saltire Argent a 8-pointed compass Sable, on a chief of the second, two 8-pointed compasses of the third.\r\nCrest: 	NA\r\nMotto: 	POSTREMO HONOR (The last thing is honor)\r\nBadge: 	On a plate within a belt Purpure edged, buckled and inscribed with the Motto in letters Argent, a 8-pointed compass Sable.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1,'Received a horizontal cut to the bridge of the nose from Davids kettle helm. No stitches were required. (2000)',1,'1999-01-09',0,'David M. Cvet',NULL,NULL,'- bad knees - have been rebuilt at least once',1,'A complete harness, with variations in the armour, a klapenvisor helm, metal gauntlets, metal breastplate, leather and metal arms, metal cuises and greeves, metal hour-glass finger gauntlets.','Salmon coloured gambeson, metal elbow cops, fencing mask, gorget.',NULL,4,'2006-01-01','Ossington',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Possesses a variety of period garments, both for men and women. ',NULL,NULL,'Brian is co-Founder of AEMMA and is its Principle Instructor.'),(4,2,7,1,'AEMMA','Anton','J','Cvet','Mr.','Mr. Anton J. Cvet','23 St. Remy Dr.',NULL,NULL,'Ottawa','ON','K2J 1A7','Canada','(613) 552-1528',NULL,NULL,'(613) 552-1528','ajcvet@aemma.org',NULL,NULL,'http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_ajcvet.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/c/cvet_aj_80.jpg','frieght aircraft pilot','M',2,0,'Wendy Smith','1960-01-07',0,NULL,NULL,1,'Assumed, November 2004','Arms:  	Quarterly, Argent and Sable an eagle displayed Azure beaked and membered Gules charged on the breast with a crescent Or and rose Argent and wearing a coronet of pearls Gules.