 his intense interest and study of the art.  \r\n'),(21,3,1,1,'AEMMA','Phil',NULL,'Groff',NULL,NULL,'139 Westwood Ave.',NULL,NULL,'Toronto','ON','M4K 2A9','Canada','(416)429-3831','416.596.2718',NULL,NULL,'pgroff@aemma.org','Dr. D. Leanoff','416.466.6699','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_pgroff.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg','Risk Manager','M',0,0,'Mary Derocher','1966-03-11',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Ph.D',NULL,0,0,NULL,0,'2000-07-15',0,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'2001-05-27','Regent Park',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Phil has appropriate 14th century garments. See his photo for what he wore at the Yonge Street Festival.',NULL,NULL,'Phil achieved his Ph.D. while training at AEMMA. He has since taken on a risk management job, which takes most of his free time. He has periodically volunteered at AEMMA events. He has a great voice, and knows the language of the medieval period.'),(23,3,3,1,'AEMMA','James',NULL,'Hobson',NULL,NULL,'95 DeCarle Circle','Unit #7',NULL,'Etobicoke','ON','M9B 3J5','Canada','416.622.7788','905.792.5064',NULL,'416.722.5152','jhobson@aemma.org',NULL,NULL,'http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_jhobson.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg','wharehouse manager','M',0,0,NULL,'1968-11-30',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'high school',NULL,0,0,NULL,0,'2001-06-17',0,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'2002-02-17','Regent Park',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'James has had job problems in the past, working as a warehouse manager.  He had gone through a period of depression in 2005-early 2006.'),(25,3,1,1,'AEMMA','Jason','','Kendall','','','131 DArcy St.','','','Toronto','ON','','Canada','416.598.1663','416.598.1663','','','jason.kendall@haggarcanada.com','Wayne Kendall','905.337.0201','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_noPhotoDbase.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg','','M',0,0,'','1973-10-02',0,NULL,'',0,'',NULL,'','','','',0,0,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,0,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(27,3,2,8,'AEMMA','Larry',NULL,'Brydon','Mr.','Mr. Larry Brydon','297 Hamilton St.',NULL,NULL,'Newmarket','ON','L3Y 3R5','Canada',NULL,'905.895.4899',NULL,NULL,'lbrydon@rogers.com','Kirsteen Brydon','905.895.4899','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_lbrydon.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/b/brydon_80.jpg','executive, Reliance Home Comfort','M',2,0,NULL,'1960-10-06',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,1,'2003-10-29',0,'Toronto Star newspaper article','2009-03-01','2009-02-09',NULL,1,'Late 14th or early 15th century, full plate harness, full legs and arms including metal segmented solarets, breastplate, mail underlying defense, hounskul helm, metal gorget, German style metal finger gauntlets.','black gambeson, metal gorget, fencing mask, period footwear (Revival), metal finger gauntlets.','Larry is an aggressive fencer and fighter, periodically, over-powering his opponents with brute strength. Through continuous training, and encouragement through instruction, his intensity has decreased a bit, but more work is needed.  His strikes will often cause injury, and bruising on his opponent.  He has good basic fencing skill, and is very fast. (Nov 2005)',2,'2005-03-06','Ossington',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Larry had lost approximately 40 lbs during training with AEMMA sometime in 2005, however, has put the poundage back on in 2006.  He used to play football at university (Mar 2006).\r\nReturned to Training Oct 2008, taking the Rapier program'),(29,3,3,1,'AEMMA','Mike','','Larsh','','','415 Scottsdale Dr.','','','Guelph','ON','N1G 2W6','Canada','','(519) 837-8796','','','mrlarsh@hotmail.com','','','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_noPhotoDbase.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg','','M',0,0,'','1980-12-07',0,NULL,'',0,'',NULL,'','','','',0,0,NULL,0,'2002-05-27',0,'','0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,0,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,''),(31,3,1,1,'AEMMA','Bryan','A.','Comyn','Mr.','Mr. Bryan A. Comyn','21 Vaughan Road','Apt#1204',NULL,'Toronto','ON','M6G 2N2','Canada',NULL,'416.651.5427',NULL,NULL,'bcomyn@rogers.com','Linda Comyn','705.671.1681','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_noPhotoDbase.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg',NULL,'M',0,0,NULL,'1974-05-18',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,0,'2003-11-17',0,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(34,3,1,1,'AEMMA','Richard','J','Gallant',NULL,NULL,'28 Winston Ave.',NULL,NULL,'Scarborough','ON','M1N 1W3','Canada','416.690.1299','416.690.1299',NULL,NULL,'ricgallant@hotmail.com',NULL,NULL,'http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_noPhotoDbase.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg','millwright','M',0,0,NULL,'1955-05-16',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'grade 12',NULL,0,0,NULL,0,'2004-01-18',0,'referred to by Matt Brundle','0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2004-01-18','St. Clair',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AEMMA: long-term absence survey - Apr 4, 2008\r\nHey David, Brian, Kel, Frank, Steve\r\n\r\nIt is too sad that I\\\\\\\'ve not kept with your wonderful training.\r\nI would like to first apologize on the fact I have forgotten some names of the AEMMA training staff.\r\n \r\nActually my intro was moving your last old school to your present school on Dupont??, but if you have moved again, Congratulations.\r\n \r\nI was introduced by Mat Brundle, who did try to keep me in the fold. I was training less than 1 year.\r\nIf only I were younger. LOL. I\\\\\\\'ll be 53 this year. Was I training about 3 years back. :(\r\n \r\nDavid, I could do it but a hand injury during hand to hand with Aldo was the true reason I stopped training. I left thinking to be back when it healed. I am a millwright mechanic and my hands are my work mates. The healing didn\\\\\\\'t happen fully for six months. By that time, being 50 and never had anything happen but a broken toe one bad sprain and a hernia, so I passed.\r\n.\r\n \r\nALL of the staff including the other disciplines training are top notch. Their help is in keeping classes with training and, well, I guess what I might be trying to say is that Oh boy Lets try,\r\nThe instructors did not approach me to train me, They wished for me to train with them.\r\nThey would freely give info and insight just by asking. Classes ran smoothly and on topic.\r\nTrainers always showed comradery, which is what drew me the most and miss the most.\r\nStudents were not allowed \\\\\\\"out of bounds nor overboard\\\\\\\" Easy to do with sword in hand :)\r\n \r\nYour rates at the time were ok with me. Now time is my problem and my Better Half says it\\\\\\\'s money.\r\nThere is nothing in memory that I would have changed.\r\n \r\nThanks for the Mail David.\r\nLets hope we meet again.\r\nRichard Gallant\r\n*********************************************\r\nhe was brought in via Matt Brundle (a neighbour of his).'),(36,3,1,1,'AEMMA','Chris','R.','Armstrong','Mr.','Mr. Chris R. Armstrong','415 Manor Road East',NULL,NULL,'Toronto','ON','M4S 1T1','Canada','(416) 488 8439','(416) 654-2513',NULL,'416 893 4598','carmstrong@interbrand.ca',NULL,NULL,'http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_carmstrong.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg',NULL,'',0,0,'Dana','1967-06-01',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'diploma','Alberta College of Art & Design',0,0,NULL,0,'2000-11-27',0,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,1,'Early 13th century harness which includes a great helm, period surcoat, butted mail shirt, leggings and footwear, kite shield.  He also has a hounskul built by Peter Fuller in Calgary.',NULL,NULL,2,'2001-05-27','Regent Park',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Chris originally came from Calgary, and was a friend of Peter Fuller (Medieval Reproductions). Peter had started a small group, 12th-13th century, sword & shield which Chris was originally part of, till he moved to Toronto, and found AEMMA. (Feb 2001).\r\n\r\nChris went and got himself married to Danna that had a child, bought a house, and disappeared from AEMMA.  He periodically visits.  Now has three kids.  Plans on returning to practice once the youngest requires less of his time. (Oct 2006)'),(38,2,20,2,'AEMMA','Luis',NULL,'Pereira','Mr.','Mr. Luis Pereira','30 Connorvale Ave',NULL,NULL,'Etobicoke','ON','M8W 4A1','Canada','416-660-0315','416-660-0315',NULL,NULL,'ktullu@gmail.com','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_lpereira.jpg','416.259.5904','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_lpereira.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg',NULL,'M',1,0,NULL,'1965-12-31',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'SSGD',NULL,0,0,NULL,1,'2001-01-14',0,NULL,'2009-09-01','2009-03-01',NULL,0,'A partial harness, has been working on it for a couple of years. Black gambeson, riveted mail shirt, metal finger gauntlets of the hour-glass style, metal & leather gorget, some arm plate, legs are not complete, no helm.','black gambeson, fencing mask, metal finger gauntlets, flat-soled footwear.',NULL,2,'2002-04-21','Regent Park',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'A bluish tunic, period leather belt, pouch, rondel dagger, leggings and flat-footwear.',NULL,NULL,'Luis trains with regularity, except during periods of life changes, such as education or job changes.  He also has a propensity to become heavily engaged with the latest computer game.  He is also a high-ranking member of the OTO.  Luis still maintains his Portuguese passport, not having a Canadian passport.'),(40,2,5,1,'AEMMA','Kelly',NULL,'Rekuta','Mr.','Mr. Kelly Rekuta','849 Bem Ave.',NULL,NULL,'Pickering','ON','L1W 1X2','Canada','(905) 839.8578','(416) 784.5888',NULL,'(905) 391-9807','krekuta@sympatico.ca','Mary Anne Rekuta',NULL,'http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_krekuta.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/r/rekuta_80.jpg','partner - Capi