can think of.  It was so long ago that I’m sure much has changed since I was there.\r\n   4. What do you/did you think of the instructors? Offer a brief explanation.\r\nExcellent!  All the instructors were knowledgeable and proficient instructors.\r\n   5. Did you feel that the monthly training fees mapped well with the services offered?  How do the fees compare to other martial arts schools you know of?\r\nAgain, I had no complaints about the fee structure.\r\n   6. How long did you train at AEMMA before leaving the Academy?\r\nI was a member for about 18 months but only really trained for about 3.\r\n   7. What caused your long-term absence (no details, just high level description)?\r\nI left fro personal, family reasons.\r\n   8. What changes or enhancements to AEMMA would be enough for you to consider returning to practices?\r\nNone to AEMMA that I can think of.\r\n   9. Would you have any general comments or opinions about AEMMA?\r\nIt’s an excellent organization and I continue to refer people to AEMMA (my AEMMA jacket makes me a walking billboard!)\r\n*******************************\r\nTracey has a history of disappearing, and re-appearing at training. His long term disappearances has seriously retarded his martial training.  Periodically, he will show up and claim that he will now be training with regularity, and will show up for one or two practices and disappear once again.'),(45,3,2,1,'AEMMA','Todd',NULL,'Teal','Mr.','Mr. Todd Teal','1031 Bertie St.',NULL,NULL,'Fort Erie','ON','L2A 5R9','Canada',NULL,'416.578.3560',NULL,NULL,'toddteal@globalsensorsystems.com','Shirley Teal','905.871.2271','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_noPhotoDbase.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg','IT professional','M',0,0,NULL,'1971-03-08',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,0,'2002-06-26',0,NULL,'0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AEMMA long-term absence survey - Apr 4, 2008\r\nHi D