     5. Did you feel that the monthly training fees mapped well with the services offered?  How do the fees compare to other martial arts schools you know of?\r\nI didn\\\\\\\'t think the fees were excessive,  but don\\\\\\\'t have any experience with any other martial arts schools.\r\n       6. How long did you train at AEMMA before leaving the Academy?\r\nThree months\r\n       7. What caused your long-term absence (no details, just high level description)?\r\nLife got in the way, and frankly I lacked the discipline to get out of bed on Sunday mornings all the time for classes. I also seriously got back in cycling again.\r\n       8. What changes or enhancements to AEMMA would be enough for you to consider returning to practices?\r\nIt would be more like me learning to be less lazy.  I\r\n       9. Would you have any general comments or opinions about AEMMA?\r\nI thought it was fun, and I may well be back once I disentangle myself from some other classes / committments I have going on.\r\n Donald Simmons\r\n\r\n**************************\r\nDonald is your classic non-martial person.  His training initially will be based on his footwork, and re-connecting his brain with his body.  Although, he may never become a fencer, there has been some notable improvement in his coordination.  He was referred to AEMMA by Ariella Elema.\r\n\r\nalternative email: dfs.engineer@gmail.com\r\n\r\nFTW: He emailed me to say he resigned on November 16, 2006.'),(168,3,8,1,'AEMMA','Matt',NULL,'Narrol','Mr.','Mr. Matt Narrol','138 Cedargrove Rd.',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','ON','L7E 2W9','Canada','905.857.7784','905.857.7784',NULL,'416.460.5170','life@rogers.com','Dianne Narrol','905.857.7784/416.523','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_noPhotoDbase.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg','student','M',0,0,NULL,'1968-05-14',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'M.S.',NULL,0,0,NULL,0,'2005-09-17',0,'ROM','0000-00-00',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,