schools you know of?\r\nFees were roughly comparable.\r\n   6. How long did you train at AEMMA before leaving the Academy?\r\nJust over 1 year.\r\n   7. What caused your long-term absence (no details, just high level description)?\r\nPrimarily personal: distance [travel between Brampton and Toronto] and unable to advance in skills (for reasons noted above).  Also the conception by some instructors that I must achieve Scholler status and acquire all [Scholler] gear even though I, personally, lack enough skill to achieve such a level and the Recruit level fulfilled my interest of the European fighting arts.\r\n   8. What changes or enhancements to AEMMA would be enough for you to consider returning to practices?\r\nAside from the personal reasons listed above, a little less intensity on achieving the Scholler level and more appreciation for the European fighting arts [as a historical or personal interest] at the Recruit level.\r\n   9. Would you have any general comments or opinions about AEMMA?\r\nI appreciate what AEMMA is doing in promoting European fighting arts in it truest form as it is often misrepresented by cinema and other ‘recreationist’ groups.  But, the level of commitment portrayed at the Recruit level appears to be too intense.  Those who will/wish to advance beyond this level will show themselves above the others.  Perhaps a “Mentor” type stage between the Recruit and Scholler level would better distinguish the Recreational to the Serious participant.\r\nSincerely,\r\nEric R'),(257,3,1,4,'AEMMA','Cameron',NULL,'Ansell','Mr.','Mr. Cameron Ansell','1280 Meredith Avenue',NULL,NULL,'Mississauga','ON','L5N 2E5','Canada','905 278-7955',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Janine','905 278-7955','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_noPhotoDbase.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg','Retired','M',0,0,'Janine','1944-03-31',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,0,'2006-05-08',0,NULL,'2006-10-15','2006-06-15','Medication: Desperol',0,NULL,NULL,NUL