L,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Incomplete record for Robin.  The first round of payments went to Shawn. Received $180 for Oct and Nov training as committed. (Oct 9 - dcvet)'),(281,3,2,3,'AEMMA','Joel','R.','Cormode','Mr.','Mr. Joel R. Cormode','89 McCaul St.','Apt 913',NULL,'Toronto','ON','M5T 2X3','Canada',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'jrcormode@yahoo.com',NULL,NULL,'http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_jcormode.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg','high school teacher','M',1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,1,'2006-10-16',0,NULL,'2007-07-15','2007-03-19',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'AEMMA: long term absence survey - Apr 4, 2008\r\nDavid,\r\nI think we discussed some of these things when I cam in and told you that I could not continue coming to AEMMA.  I like surveys.  Here you go\r\n1.  Why did you visit AEMMA in the first place?\r\nI know both Brian and Kel through the SCA and I have a life long interest in swordmanship.\r\n2.  Did the training at AEMMA meet your expectations while training? If not, what was missing?\r\nYes and no.  Having done other martial activities in the past I found myself in the recruit classes at times impatient to move on to more challanging activities.  At the same time I recognized the impatience for what it was and accepted the discipline of the program in order to develop the skills that were being taught.  I did find my own lack of measurable progress frustrating.\r\nI found the requirements to move to the next level of training to be vague.  I was never certain and am still not certain what a person must do.\r\nThat the Fiore and other manuscripts are not available in tangible form is disappointing.  The electronic versions are difficult to access and there is no indication which of the various electronic versions is considered the authoritative one by the instructors.\r\nThe sword in two hands is of much greater interest to me than the arming sword.  The sword in two hands is not taught at the recruit level.  I understand the reasons why AEMMA is set up that way but I did find it disappointing.\r\n3.  What recommendations would you suggest to improve AEMMA, its training facilities, training program, its people?\r\nNone that I did not address already in #2.\r\n4.  What do you/did you think of the instructors? Offer a brief explanation.\r\nIn terms of specific analysis of individuals?  I am not a match for Kel\\\\\\\'s teaching style.  That is something that will vary from person to person. \r\nI understand the importance of having senior members of the salle teach, but at times it created a chaotic feeling.\r\n5.  Did you feel that the monthly training fees mapped well with the services offered?  How do the fees compare to other martial arts schools you know of?\r\nI do not recall what I paid for Tae Kwon Do back in 1995, but I am certain that in absolute dollars AEMMA is probably less expensive.  I know that it is less than some of the martial arts organizations I have investigated in the past year or so.  More than the price however I found the payment plan off-putting.  Requiring payment for 6 months in advance may be good business sense (and perhaps even demonstrates commitment on the part of the student) but it was something I found to be a financial burden.\r\nThe only service offered by AEMMA I ever used were the AEMMA classes so I cannot comment outside of that.\r\n6.  How long did you train at AEMMA before leaving the Academy?\r\nOff and on from early 2004 to mid 2007.  At first I went to two sessions a week but towards the end I could only come to one session a week.\r\n7.  What caused your long-term absence (no details, just high level description)?\r\nCost and schedule.  In spite of AEMMA\\\\\\\'s low cost compared to other martial arts organizations I found that I could not afford it.  Evening sessions (particularly late evening sessions) were a difficult time for me to attend.  Sunday morning sessions are impossible for me to attend.\r\n8.  What changes or enhancements to AEMMA would be enough for you to consider returning to practices?\r\nAfternoon sessions would fit my own schedule much more easily than evening sessions. \r\n9.  Would you have any general comments or opinions about AEMMA?\r\nI enjoyed the program and regret that I cannot continue in it.  I do recommend it to people I meet who show an interest in swordsmanship.\r\nJoel Cormode\r\n**************************************\r\nJoel had trained with AEMMA approximately 18 months ago, but left due to work and domestic issues.  He has returned, training only Mondays as casual until his schedule and free time improves. (Oct 2006 - dcvet)\r\nJoel had submitted 4 post-dated cheques @ $65, last cheque dated Jun 15 2007 (Mar 19, 2007 - dcvet)'),(282,3,4,2,'AEMMA','Kirill',NULL,'Kaplun','Mr.',NULL,'505 Cummer Ave',NULL,NULL,'North York','ON','L6A 2N5','Canada','416 222-2852',NULL,NULL,'416 271 4270','kirill187@hotmail.com',NULL,'416 222 2852','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_kirill.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg','Call Center Supervisor','M',0,0,NULL,'1985-04-18',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,1,'2006-11-11',0,'AEMMA website','2007-06-30','2007-06-09',NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(283,3,1,4,'AEMMA','Gillian',NULL,'Chesnais','Mr.',NULL,'12 Sudbury Street','Unit 101',NULL,'Toronto','ON','M2J 3W7','Canada','416 598-5405',NULL,NULL,'416 666-5467','deamonkicker@hotmail.com','Nicole Chesnais','416 670-5403','http://www.aemma.org/images/bio_photos/bio_gchesnais.jpg','http://www.aemma.org/arms/a/aemma_80.jpg','student','M',0,0,NULL,'1990-04-02',0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,1,'2006-11-06',0,NULL,'2008-05-15','2007-12-23','secondary contact: Alain Chesnais, 416-598-5405',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(284,3,2,3,'AEMMA','Ilian',NULL,'Iliev'